        "text": "<@UC2A2ARPT> From a Free Software perspective, most of what you see via browser devtools isn't source. The GPL definition is \"_The source code for a work means the preferred form of the work for making modifications to it.\"_ A Web site that has undergone a build step is not published as source. It's still very helpful for exploring, even reverse engineering, of course. A lot better than native code. But I guess WASM will put Web sites on the level of apps if it ever gets widely adopted.",
